1
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,080
Hi, David.

2
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,400
Are you flirting with my David?

3
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:17,360
Well, whoever plays it right, gets it, Chai!

4
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:18,800
If Chai is throwing a birthday party...

5
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,840
Mr. Glam might be there.

6
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,000
I'll handle tonight.

7
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:29,600
Excuse me, 1 spicy water hyacinth, please.

8
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,720
If you're bringing Larb, just the Larb, okay?

9
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:31,520
But Blood...

10
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:34,840
I'll go get it at that table myself!

11
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:35,760
Madam, what are you doing?

12
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:36,960
If I don't have it my way,

13
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:40,040
I guess there will be some blood!

14
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:02,880
Happy birthday to you...

15
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:08,280
Happy birthday to you...

16
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:14,720
Happy birthday...

17
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:18,720
Happy birthday to you.

18
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:23,880
Happy birthday, Chai.

19
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:25,320
Be happy, always.

20
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:26,280
Thank you so much.

21
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:30,280
Wishing you a house full of children and a town full of grandchildren!

22
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,120
Thank you.

23
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:33,120
I'll change from 14 tims a day...

24
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,800
to 28 times a day...alright?

25
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,200
Wow, you're so strong!

26
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,920
But I'm not married yet.

27
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,960
So no, I don't want any babies.

28
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,920
Make a wish!

29
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:48,240
I will!

30
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:06,120
You're my wish!

31
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:13,240
Tid-Gift!

32
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:15,280
You, die!

33
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,080
You, go to hell!

34
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:19,480
Go to hell!

35
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,400
Tid-Gift!

36
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,120
I was having a good dream...

37
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:26,120
yet you still came to haunt me!

38
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,880
Na-mo, conceal me whole.

39
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:32,520
Create a veil, seal all harm.

40
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,480
Na-jang-ngang, bind this body still.

41
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,560
Na-a-u, u-i-a,

42
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:39,080
U-i-a, u-e!

43
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:39,960
Wait, that's not it.

44
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,320
Na-mo, conceal me whole.

45
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,360
Create a veil, seal all harm.

46
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,600
Na-jang-ngang, bind this body still.

47
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,360
Na-a-u, let karmic spirits and vengeful souls see me not.

48
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:47,880
Buddhang, vanish from their sight.

49
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:48,800
Dhammang, shield this body.

50
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,640
Sanghang, seal it from view.

51
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,640
Sadhu.

52
00:03:57,240 --> 00:04:00,240
Hey, where did the bridge go?

53
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,520
Oh, this is nice.

54
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,920
Looks like the table is not tilted anymore.

55
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:05,320
This is easier to put things on the table.

56
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:08,320
Eh? Where did she go so early?

57
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:16,720
Siri.

58
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,520
Madam is not here?

59
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,920
That's what I'm wondering. She was here earlier.

60
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,440
Maybe she has some other business to deal with.

61
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,600
What other business?

62
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,640
Don't you all think you need to work too?

63
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:29,560
See? These papers! They need to be signed.

64
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,440
Yet, she still went out.

65
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:33,760
If she weren't my boss, I would scold her.

66
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,520
But you are scolding her right now.

67
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,800
This is nothing.

68
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:40,440
Just wait, I bet she's out at the temple buying new amulets to worship or something.

69
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:44,440
Look at this place! Our office is turning into a damn shrine.

70
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,840
Ugh. Just talking about it makes me mad!

71
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:48,160
Ouch.

72
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,160
Oh!

73
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:54,560
Oh, you've been here this whole time?

74
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,640
Yes.

75
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:56,840
Sadhu.

76
00:04:56,840 --> 00:05:00,560
Wow! Father Son's hiding spell actually works!

77
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:03,720
Madam, you camouflaged with the wall!

78
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,440
No one in their right mind could've seen you!

79
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,960
If you don't believe it, don't disrespect it.

80
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:09,760
I heard what you said about me too, Siri!

81
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,680
So, what's up with you two?

82
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,640
Anything on Glam?

83
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:14,600
Yes, Madam.

84
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,680
What is it?

85
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,720
Same as before, Madam.

86
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:20,720
What? Has anyone come up with anything?

87
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:23,320
Anything new?

88
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,680
Oh, what's up, Chai?

89
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,200
Are you with Kreetha?

90
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,920
I couldn't reach Kreetha.

91
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,560
I'd like to invite you both to my birthday party tonight.

92
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,440
Tonight?

93
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:38,240
Oh, I'll see if I can make it.

94
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,480
Let me know, alright?

95
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,480
I will, goodbye.

96
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,800
Chai is throwing a birthday party tonight.

97
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,960
He invited both of us.

98
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:47,560
I won't be able to make it.

99
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,560
I got a flight tonight.

100
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,200
Wait a minute!

101
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,280
Mr. Glam and Chai might be pretty close.

102
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:59,000
If Chai is throwing a birthday party tonight,

103
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,440
Mr. Glam might be there.

104
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:03,040
That's true!

105
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,320
Or should I call in tonight?

106
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,000
That won't be necessary.

107
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,680
I'll handle tonight.

108
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:12,320
Siri, go get ready.

109
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,320
Absolutely, Madam.

110
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,240
Choose one.

111
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,000
What? Siri!

112
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,240
We're gonna go spy on them, we're not starting a war!

113
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,680
Well, you didn't tell me.

114
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,760
Put them away!

115
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:29,080
Damn it!

116
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,880
Be careful!

117
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:32,800
I'm sorry, it slipped.

118
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,800
Good thing I have my concealment spell.

119
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,080
Really?

120
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:42,400
That's fantastic.

121
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,400
Madam, can I see it again?

122
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:49,520
I really don't wanna show off...

123
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:53,520
but...if you all wanna see it, I'll do it.

124
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,000
Na-a-u, u-i-a,

125
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:00,960
U-i-a, u-e!

126
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,560
Madam Porn, where have you gone?

127
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,800
Oh my god, I can't believe this!

128
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,880
Madam, where are you?

129
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:09,160
Madam Porn, where are you? Where are you?

130
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,160
It really works!

131
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:13,640
Hey, Kreetha, All-New!

132
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,720
Madam Porn isn't here...

133
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:18,240
and I happen to know where she hides her money.

134
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,480
Shall we steal it?

135
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,480
You guys!

136
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,520
This is a new luxurious item.

137
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:32,800
From Paris, France.

138
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:36,120
Hey, that's pretty. Which brand is that?

139
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,200
You wouldn't know it.

140
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,280
This brand is very famous in France.

141
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:40,880
Tell me in case I know it!

142
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,000
It's Coachly.

143
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,320
Huh, is it?

144
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:44,240
Yeah.

145
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,120
That sounds familiar.

146
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,880
Coachly Wanta?

147
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,720
Coachly Wantha Abhivadana, alright?

148
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,920
Oh, Abivadana? That must be pricey...

149
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:51,600
It's pretty...

150
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:55,600
I guess it must be more than 40,000 Baht.

151
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,120
But I got it at a very good price.

152
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,320
It was on sale.

153
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,240
How much is it?

154
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:02,640
It's only 299 Baht!

155
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:05,920
What leather is that? Is it from a pig? It's pink.

156
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,960
It's from Crocaland.

157
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:09,200
Crocaland?

158
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,240
A crocodile?

159
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,280
A monitor lizard.

160
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,800
Definitely from a monitor lizard.

161
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,880
It's pretty, right?

162
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:17,840
Yes, it is.

163
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:18,680
Right.

164
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,480
It suits you well.

165
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,120
Right.

166
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:23,040
Let's talk about something else.

167
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:26,720
Sky, the price tag is still here.

168
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,360
Well, other people would know that I got it from France.

169
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,800
What's up, everyone?

170
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,960
Chai!

171
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,240
Sky is showing off her new purse.

172
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,400
Wow, that is beautiful.

173
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,720
Aren't you guys flying today?

174
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,080
We just got here.

175
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:37,880
We just got back.

176
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:38,960
I just got back from France.

177
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,200
Oh, you must be free, then.

178
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:42,080
I'm inviting you both...

179
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,480
to my birthday party.

180
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,560
Ooh, now, we're talking.

181
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,600
Well, but there are three people sitting here...

182
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,560
Oh.

183
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,760
There are three of you here?

184
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,560
Three...

185
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:54,080
Oh, I've noticed that just now but I'm still inviting just the two of you.

186
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:57,640
Hey, there must be some beef between these two.

187
00:08:57,640 --> 00:09:01,600
That's what I thought.

188
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:06,480
Doesn't matter if you invite me, I'm not going.

189
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,200
Glad you're aware of it.

190
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,520
So I don't have to ask.

191
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:11,920
But we're all friends.

192
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,320
Real friends don't pull this kind of shit.

193
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:18,160
Right, real friends don't pull this kind of shit.

194
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:20,440
Remind me again, who did it first?

195
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:21,760
Don't make me say it, Chai.

196
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,520
Say it!

197
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,440
I'm not saying it.

198
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,440
Say it!

199
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:27,680
Say it!

200
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,160
Wait until my turn.

201
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,280
Well, say it!

202
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,280
If you're not gonna say it, then keep it shut.

203
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:32,960
I'll keep it shut.

204
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,040
I'll keep it shut.

205
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,360
I don't wanna say anything.

206
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,640
I'm only saying this because I wanna know.

207
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,600
You know it but you said you wouldn't say it.

208
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,400
You do too but you said you wouldn't say it.

209
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,960
But you said you're not gonna say it.

210
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:46,640
I don't know anything but I'm saying this because I wanna know.

211
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:48,320
Oh, so who says what?

212
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,160
You and I are the only two speaking.

213
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,560
Those two know but they wouldn't say it.

214
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,760
Well, I'm not saying it.

215
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,720
Neither am I.

216
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:55,480
Hang on, you two...

217
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:59,000
I'm begging you, please tell us.

218
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,080
We really wanna know.

219
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,080
Right.

220
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,200
Hi, Mr. David.

221
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,160
Hello, Miss Tid-Gift.

222
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,880
Wow, your Thai's gotten better.

223
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,840
Not really.

224
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,920
Welcome back to Thailand.

225
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:25,880
Thank you very much.

226
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,280
Oh.

227
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,920
My lipstick...

228
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,600
Pardon?

229
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,880
I've dropped my lipstick.

230
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,880
Please hold this for me, would you?

231
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,440
I'm giving this back to you.

232
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,440
Thank you.

233
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,040
What's wrong with you?

234
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,040
Are you flirting with my David?

235
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,600
Flirting?

236
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,880
Mr. David...

237
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:03,640
got me flowers, can't you see?

238
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:05,160
But he and I are talking now.

239
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,600
I just got back from a flight with him.

240
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,960
And?

241
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:09,280
I got here first!

242
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,920
And?

243
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,160
I was here first, okay?

244
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:17,160
Well, whoever plays it right, gets it, Chai!

245
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,840
Ooh, my arm...

246
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:37,120
Oh, so that's why...

247
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,680
They fought over a guy.

248
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,560
That's nonsense.

249
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:43,560
Really. Let me tell you. Sky and I...

250
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:46,720
we've been flying together for thousands of flights and we never fight.

251
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,920
That's right.

252
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:50,600
Captain David, we flew with him before, right?

253
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,280
That's right.

254
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,400
We didn't fight over him.

255
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:56,400
Even though he glanced at me more than he did Sky...

256
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:59,360
That's not it.

257
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,920
But Captain David...

258
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,040
he liked looking at my curves...

259
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,680
when I served him the meal.

260
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:05,880
And when I leaned over,

261
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:08,280
he always peeked at me.

262
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:09,400
Why would he peek at you?

263
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,920
You look like an animal.

264
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:11,640
Damn you!

265
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:12,920
You said I looked like an animal!

266
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,360
Well, that's a fact.

267
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:16,760
Well, that might be true but it came out of your mouth.

268
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:18,800
And what's the problem? I got a mouth to speak.

269
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:19,680
And you think you're the only person with a mouth?

270
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:20,960
I got a mouth too.

271
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,160
I'm prettier than you.

272
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:23,160
How?

273
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,160
In every way.

274
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:24,840
Point it out.

275
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,440
I'll hit you with this purse!

276
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,280
I got my feet to kick you!

277
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:27,720
What?

278
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,920
You want a piece of me, Sky?

